Step by step:

playbook/
├── playbook-roles-vsftpd.yml
└── roles/
    └── vsftpd/
        ├── files/
        │   └── vsftpd.conf
        └── tasks/
            └── main.yml

Step 1. navigate to playbook directory and create the roles directory if it does not exist:
  cd ~/playbook
  mkdir roles

Step 2. Change into the roles directory and create the vsftpd role directory with the required subdirectories:
  cd roles
  mkdir -p vsftpd/{files,tasks}

Step 3. Create the vsftpd.conf file in the files subdirectory. 
This file will contain the vsftpd configuration settings. 
we can use the default configuration file or create a custom one. 
  mentioed in the vsftpd.conf file
  
Step 4. Create the main.yml file in the tasks subdirectory. 
This file will contain the tasks that will be executed by the vsftpd role.
  Mentioned in the main.yml file
  
Step 5. Create the playbook-roles-vsftpd.yml file in the playbook directory. 
This file will include the vsftpd role. 
  Mentioed i the playbook-roles-vsftpd.yml file.
  
step 6. Ru bellow command to crete Ansible role that installs and runs the vsftpd FTP server.
  ansible-playbook playbook-roles-vsftpd.yml
